# Project Rules — AI Dev Trends Explorer

## Tech Stack
- Next.js (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons
- Frontend only (no backend or database for v1)

## Architecture Guidelines
- Use src/ directory structure
- Prefer small reusable components
- Components should be organized by feature folder
- Keep pages minimal and delegate UI to components
- Use strongly typed data structures

## Data Strategy
- Use static local data for tools, workflows, and trends
- Store data under src/data/
- Avoid APIs or external services in v1

## UI Guidelines
- Dark modern design
- Clean spacing and strong hierarchy
- Use subtle animations only when useful
- Avoid flashy or excessive motion
- Mobile responsive by default

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict typing preferred
- Prefer functional React components
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies
- Keep code readable and modular

## Workflow Expectations
When implementing features:

1. Keep changes scoped
2. Do not rewrite unrelated files
3. Follow existing architecture
4. Run lint and build after major changes

## Commands

Run development server:

npm run dev

Run lint:

npm run lint

Verify production build:

npm run build
